-- Ghana Beats Cape Verde 2-0 in Africa Cup of Nations Quarterfinal
-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 2013-02-02T18:30:14Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-02-02/ghana-beats-cape-verde-2-0-in-africa-cup-of-nations-quarterfinal.html
Ghana defeated Cape Verde 2-0 in the
quarterfinals of soccer’s Africa Cup of Nations.  Mubarak Wakaso had both goals for Ghana in Port Elizabeth.
South Africa. He opened the scoring with a penalty kick in the
54th minute and clinched the victory in second-half stoppage
time on a counterattack as Cape Verde pushed for the tying goal.  Ghana advances to the Feb. 6 semifinals against the winner
of tomorrow’s match between  Burkina Faso  and Togo. Host South
Africa meets Mali in today’s other quarterfinal, with the winner
facing  Ivory Coast  or Nigeria.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  